body:
This PR tries to reintroduce the module names addition, see https://github.com/llvm/circt/pull/3195

The above PR broke the release build with clang, see https://github.com/llvm/circt/runs/6609024322
I invested a substantial amount of time to figure out what the problem is, but in the end I have to conclude that I either introduced UB or that clang might be bugged in a very weird way. 

Changing 

```c++
    if (bufferOp.initValues().hasValue()) {
      subModuleName += "_init";
      ArrayAttr values = bufferOp.initValues().getValue();
      for (const Attribute e : values) {
        assert(e.isa<IntegerAttr>());
        subModuleName +=
            "_" + std::to_string(e.dyn_cast<IntegerAttr>().getInt());
      }
    }
```

to 

```c++
    if (bufferOp.initValues().hasValue()) {
      subModuleName += "_init";
      for (const Attribute e : bufferOp.initValues().getValue()) {
        assert(e.isa<IntegerAttr>());
        subModuleName +=
            "_" + std::to_string(e.dyn_cast<IntegerAttr>().getInt());
      }
    }
```

Causes the test to crash with a segfault. Note that I checked that the assertion is indeed valid in all cases by inserting if statements that would cause visible side-effects.

Any suggestions on how we want to continue with that issue?
